Nigeria  and the European Union signed
a 197 million-euro ($249.4 million) agreement to support the
West African nation,  ThisDay  reported, citing Minister of
National Planning Shamsuddeen Usman.  The money will be used to strengthen Nigeriaâ€™s judicial
system, help fight drugs and organized crime, and improve water
and sanitation, the Lagos-based newspaper said. They will also
be used to support improving the electoral system ahead of the
general elections in 2015, it said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
